We recommend that the Local Chief Executive direct the Municipal Accountant to:

Prepare the necessary adjusting entries in the books by debiting Due to GOCCs amounting to ₱829,857.12 and crediting Share from PCSO amounting to ₱182,949.69 and Prior Period Adjustments amounting to ₱646,907.43; 

Restate the CY 2021 Consolidated Financial Statement to reflect the necessary adjusting entries for prior years’ receipt of Share from PCSO;

Ensure that the subsequent Lotto and STL Shares received from PCSO are correctly recorded in the appropriate book;

Maintain a Special Account and Subsidiary Ledgers under the General Fund-Proper for the receipt and utilization of Lotto and STL Shares received from PCSO.


We also recommend that the Local Chief Executive direct the Local Finance Committee to endorse the passage of an appropriate supplemental appropriation ordinance to authorize the use and disbursement of the Lotto and STL Shares received from PCSO per the purpose intended and thereafter ensure the submission of Fund Utilization Report to the PCSO in accordance with the MOA.

We have recommended that the LCE direct the:

Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with a complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;


Municipal Engineer and Municipal Accountant determine, or if not practicable, estimate the carrying amount of the assets replaced taking into consideration the cost, age and condition of the replaced asset;

Thereafter, Municipal Accountant to make necessary adjustments in the Local Road Networks account for the derecognition of the replaced assets.;

Municipal Accountant prepare and maintain subsidiary ledgers for each component, containing distinctive information such as measurement of the project component to facilitate in future derecognition of assets in the book of accounts as a result of rehabilitation or improvements made.

