We have recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
Utilize the LDRRMF in accordance with PPAs detailed in the LDRRMFIP;
Enjoin the MDRRMC to comply with the provisions of RA 10121 and JMC in prioritizing PPAs to be included in the LDRRMFIP;
Observe compliance with the minimum standards for disaster preparedness to minimize the effect of calamities;
Organize and revisit the Municipality’s plantilla and sources of funds to be able to create a position that would assist the MDRRMO in the aspects of administration and trainings; research and planning; and operations and warning; and
Prepare and submit monthly report on sources and utilization of DRRMF

4.3. With the foregoing, we recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct
The Bids and Awards Committee to prepare and submit the Annual Procurement Plan prior the start of the year based on the Approved Budget of the Municipality;

The Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator and Municipal Engineer to submit complete list of all on-going government projects/programs/activities and those that are to be implemented during the year; 

The Municipal Engineer to ensure that the billboards displayed for projects will be fabricated by the contractor based on what was programmed in the Program of Work; and

The MPDC and Municipal Engineer to inform the audit team and Supervising Auditor that the appropriate project signboards and/or public notices are already posted.

For the observations noted, we reiterated the following recommendations:
The GSO-Designate to maintain property cards per category of PPE;
The Accounting Unit to maintain complete property ledger cards for all PPE owned by the agency;
The GSO-Designate and Accounting Unit to exert effort in reconciling their records;
The Accounting Unit to exert effort in locating or producing the documents to support the legitimacy of the unreconciled PPE account balances and hereafter, strengthen the control over documentation of all financial transactions; and
The Accounting Unit to disclose in their notes the gross carrying amount of any fully depreciated property, plant and equipment that is still in use and the carrying amount of property, plant and equipment retired from active use and held for disposal.
Additionally, we recommended that the LCE direct the:
Accountable Officers to return to the GSO Designate the unserviceable properties;
Employees of DepEd, DILG, PNP and other national offices to seek clearance from the municipality upon their reassignment or retirement so that any PPEs assigned to them may be reported/turned over to the GSO-Designate;
GSO Designate to cancel the PARE related to the unserviceable properties turned-over to her; and
The Municipal Inventory and Disposal Committee to initiate the disposal in accordance with the requirements provided in COA Circular No. 92-386 dated October 20, 1992 and Section 79 of PD No. 1445 to avoid further deterioration due to natural elements and possible loss due to theft and loss of value, generate additional funds, if found valuable and sold.

